##"FATHER SENDS CAR TO PICK UP SON BACK TO JINGZHOU" , police say

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

This is a comprehensive report by thepaper.cn

A man posted on his Weibo account on Thursday that he had returned to Jingzhou from Tianmen via his father's "official" vehicle after roads were closed in Hubei Province, raising questions from netizens.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
He also posted a video saying "bye-bye Tianmen" .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Since 1300 hours on January 24,2020, Tianmen has closed the city's road access, including provincial roads, county and township roads, village roads, all vehicles and personnel are prohibited.

Separately, euamotter posted alipay's annual bill on its Weibo Account on Jan. 6, showing a total expenditure of more than 2.86 million yuan for 2019.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A number of related topics are trending on Weibo.

Many netizens comment: Your father wants to lose Jingzhou carelessly.

Ma Mei ben Mei: Carelessly Losing Jingzhou

Xiaofeiyan and Hai: The power faction is a lie

Dust Point: Oh, pit dad + 1, good ~ estimated has been beaten by Dad.

Ma Mei ben Mei: Carelessly Losing Jingzhou

Xiaofeiyan and Hai: The power faction is a lie

Dust Point: Oh, pit dad + 1, good ~ estimated has been beaten by Dad.

His father, he Yanfang, a section chief of Jingzhou's Commerce Department, had no right to send a car to pick him up from Tianmen, the man said in an apology posted on his microblog early Sunday. As he was eager to return home, his father used his friendship to contact a return vehicle of living materials in Tianmen to bring him back. "I was so vain that I claimed on the Internet that my father sent a car to pick me up. "

He also explained that the screenshot of alipay's annual bill was a running account of the company's operations, not one given by his father.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to Zhongqingbao Zhongqing.com, public information shows that he Yanfang is the head of the market operation and regulation section of Jingzhou Municipal Bureau of Commerce. He was not immediately available for comment when contacted repeatedly.

Police: Relevant departments are investigating and verifying

In the early hours of Thursday,@jingzhou posted a message saying he hao had publicly apologized on the Internet and that authorities were investigating the case further.
